description: The heavy rains that caused the suspensions and diversions are part of broader adverse weather conditions affecting the Gulf Peninsula. In Oman, heavy rainfall has led to tragic consequences with at least 18 fatalities reported in recent days. Dubai itself faced unprecedented flooding, impacting transportation, retail locations like Dubai Mall and Mall of the Emirates, and even the metro system where water pooled ankle-deep in some stations.
title: Chaos in Dubai; flights hit, families stranded at airport

description: Deputy CM Fadnavis elaborates on Mahayuti's LS poll prospects, emphasizing the significance of coalition politics, BJP's growth, challenges of infighting, and the importance of party discipline ahead of the first phase of LS polls on April 19.
title: Coalitions a reality we must learn to live with: Fadnavis

description: In Lucknow, a man killed his daughter over a relationship. Police caught him in Gudamba. An FIR under IPC 302 was filed.
title: Dad finds class 10 girl talking to boy over phone, kills her

description: MeitY strengthens India's cybersecurity posture by enhancing CCTV security through encryption, penetration testing, and role-based access protocols, focusing on wireless and physical security measures to prevent unauthorized access and cyberattacks.
title: Govt mandates new rules for CCTV cameras: Here's what the order says

description: A man and his son were arrested in Delhi for the honour killing of his daughter and cousin, both fruit vendors. The victims had deep neck wounds and were found with their throats slit in North Gonda.
title: Delhi man colludes with son to kill daughter, cousin for 'honour'

description: Telangana's Ananya Reddy, securing UPSC third rank, aspires for IAS to enhance people-centric governance. With roots in Mahbubnagar, Delhi University alumna focused on Civils prep with limited resources, opting for anthropology.
title: Telangana girl cracks Civils, gets 3rd rank in 1st attempt

description: AI girlfriends may surpass dating apps, with a man spending $10,000 monthly on AI chatbots. Greg Isenberg foresees a billion-dollar market, comparing it to Match Group's success. Virtual companions like Candy.ai and Cupid.ai gain traction, despite privacy risks.
title: Why ‘AI girlfriends’ may be a ‘problem’ for dating apps

description: After Chennai Super Kings' triumph against Mumbai Indians at the Wankhede Stadium in Mumbai during their IPL 2024 encounter on Sunday, an intriguing incident captured the attention of spectators. As the cricketers made their way to the team bus, ex-Indian batsman Suresh Raina was observed helping Mahendra Singh Dhoni, who appeared to be having difficulty walking.
title: Watch: Suresh Raina supports a limping MS Dhoni

description: US announces sanctions on Iran's missile and drone programs. Allies, including Israel, coordinate for a response. Measures aim to erode UAV capabilities. US continues to hold Iran accountable for supporting terrorist groups and actions.
title: US to impose new sanctions against Iran after attack on Israel

description: Amid safety concerns and Middle East conflict passions, USC cancels Asna Tabassum's valedictorian speech. She criticizes the decision, linking it to anti-Palestinian hatred. Hate crimes against various groups are on the rise in the U.S.
title: California university cancels Muslim valedictorian's speech

description: On Tuesday, Rajasthan Royals secured a sensational two-wicket win against Kolkata Knight Riders in the Indian Premier League, courtesy of Jos Buttler's unbeaten century. Buttler's remarkable performance guided his team to successfully chase down an imposing target of 224 runs. Despite facing a formidable total of 223/6 earlier, powered by Sunil Narine's explosive innings of 109 runs for KKR, Buttler's heroic knock as an impact substitute kept Rajasthan Royals in contention throughout the chase, even amidst the loss of partners at regular intervals.
title: Watch: Shah Rukh Khan embraces Buttler with a hug
In Lakshadweep, boats out to catch floating votes

description: The Congress party is preparing to contest its lowest number of seats ever in the upcoming Lok Sabha elections, drawing parallels with its strategy in 2004 when it formed alliances to defeat the BJP-led NDA. The party is likely to contest around 330 seats, significantly fewer than in 2004, due to alliances with various regional parties in states like Maharashtra, West Bengal, and Uttar Pradesh. .
title: Cong contests fewer seats in LS polls than ever, hopes less is more

description: In Donald Trump's hush money trial, seven jurors have been seated after two days of selection, with more to be chosen on Thursday. Trump faces 34 felony counts of falsifying business records related to alleged payoffs to Stormy Daniels, Karen McDougal, and a Trump Tower doorman. Prosecutors seek fines for Trump's social media comments violating a gag order.
title: Seven jurors seated in Trump's hush money trial
